# Ignore Nix results
result
result-*

# Ignore hardware configs (they differ per machine, avoid merge conflicts)
# NOTE: You usually want to commit hardware-configuration.nix, 
# but if you want to avoid conflicts, ignore them and regenerate on install.
# Best practice for personal repos: Commit them. 
# Best practice for teams: Ignore them. 
# For this guide, we assume personal repo, so we DO NOT ignore hardware-configuration.nix
# However, ignore secrets:
secrets/*.key
secrets/*.txt
